<div class="mdui-typo"><h1 id="slip-v">slip <strong><em>v</em></strong></h1>
<p>英 /slɪp/    美 /slɪp/  </p>
<h2 id="_1">释义</h2>
<h4 id="1">1.★ <strong>滑动；滑倒；滑落：</strong></h4>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>The boat slips through the water.
船在水上轻快地滑行。</p></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>Be careful! Don’t <strong>slip on</strong> the wet floor.
地板湿，小心别滑倒！</p><footer>北师大⑧ – 22</footer></div>

<h4 id="2">2.★ <strong>溜；悄悄逝去：</strong></h4>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>Time is <strong>slipping away</strong>.
时间悄悄地流逝。</p></div>

<h4 id="3">3.<strong>把...悄悄地放在；(把...) (迅速地) 穿上 / 脱下</strong></h4>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>He slipped the ring on her finger.
他把戒指悄悄地戴在她的手指上。</p></div>

<h4 id="4">4.<strong>错过；被...遗忘 / 忽略：</strong></h4>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>— Have you brought my book?
你把我的书拿来了吗？</p></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>— Oh, I’m sorry. It <strong>slipped my mind</strong>.
哦，对不起，我忘了。</p></div>

<h2 id="_2">真题解析</h2>
<ol>
<li>Seeing the big crowd coming towards him, he started to run down the hill, but <strong><em>_</em></strong>_ (滑倒) and went down on his hands and knees in the melting snow.  （2014 湖北改）  </li>
</ol>
<p>答案：
1. slipped  </p></div>